The paper deals with wireless communication and algorithms for scheduling communication requests, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of geometric path loss and interference models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes efficient algorithms for solving the scheduling problem, which falls under the sub-category of Algorithms (cs.AL).
